The paper deals with the problem of representing matrices in a sparse and exact manner, which is a fundamental problem in database applications. The problem is motivated by the need to explain data in a parsimonious way, which suggests that it is related to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The use of trees and linear orders to structure the data suggests that it is also related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of weighted rectangles to represent the data suggests that it is related to information theory (cs.IT).
